description: The States of Jersey announce commitment to designating a Marine Park and a short film is produced for promotion/to raise awareness.
Report outlining the potential opportunities and value of a ‘low impact’ model for Jersey’s fishing fleet is submitted to the States of Jersey.
A fisheries Working Group is established to develop ‘low-impact’ fisheries.
Snorkel trail launched, providing a case study for increased recreation, education and well-being opportunities from a Marine Park.
Creating carbon offsetting schemes for protected areas in Aruba, Bonaire, Curacao and St Maarten
Water quality monitoring Aruba MPA and wetlands
Recovery of Acroporids in Bonaire: Historical losses and future recovery potential
Bus transport marine education program (MEP) and youth marine ranger program – Curacao
Climate control room for the new Marine Field Station on Saba;
Assessing the coral and ichthyofaunal abundance and diversity of mesophotic reefs around Sint Eustatius
The Sea We Breathe online experience and associated classroom materials
An includive and diverse three-tier internship programme is developed and launched
An Ocean Observatory is established to support community engagement and citizen science
